# Agent rules

## Application map (this repository)

Turborepo monorepo. Main surfaces:

| Area | Package / app | Role |
|------|-----------------|------|
| Commerce API | `apps/medusa` | Medusa v2 backend (products, carts, orders, payments, inventory, regions). Default dev URL `http://localhost:9000`. |
| Storefront | `apps/storefront` | Public Next.js shop. Dev `http://localhost:3000`. |
| Staff admin | `apps/admin` | Next.js staff UI, POS, devices, API routes with session + RBAC. Dev `http://localhost:3001`. |
| Internal Express | `apps/api` | Health, compliance, webhooks; uses `PORT` or **4000**. Dev `http://localhost:4000`. |
| Local POS agent | `apps/terminal-agent` | Loopback HTTP print/drawer agent. Default **`http://127.0.0.1:17711`** (`TERMINAL_AGENT_PORT`). |
| Shared libs | `packages/*` | `sdk`, `platform-data`, `database`, `printer-core`, `validation`, etc. |

## Data and security boundaries

- **Medusa** is the source of truth for products, carts, orders, payments, and inventory.
- **Supabase** holds platform data (identity, RBAC, POS devices, offline queue metadata, CMS copy where wired) per ADR patterns in the repo.
- Do not move commerce-of-record writes into Supabase.
- Staff actions go through Next.js admin API routes with session checks.
- Storefront env must not expose server-only secrets (`MEDUSA_SECRET_API_KEY`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, internal API keys).
- Local POS hardware uses `apps/terminal-agent` on loopback only; browsers or admin call it **after** Medusa-backed sale success (or documented offline flows).
- Prefer extending existing modules over parallel utilities (DRY).

## Local development: single command

From the **repository root**, use:

```bash
pnpm run dev
```

This runs **`pnpm kill-ports`** then **`turbo dev`**, which starts **every workspace that defines a `dev` script** in parallel (storefront, admin, Medusa, API, terminal-agent, and any other package with `dev`). Treat it as the default way to run the **full local application stack** for integration work.

- **Terminal agent URL:** `http://127.0.0.1:17711` (receipt print, open drawer, `/health`, `/status`). Configure via `.env` / `.env.example` (`TERMINAL_AGENT_PORT`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_TERMINAL_AGENT_*`, device name, Supabase sync for `pos_devices` when used).
- Other common dev ports (see `scripts/kill-project-ports.js` for what gets cleared before dev): **3000**, **3001**, **4000**, **9000**. Port **17711** is not in that kill list; stop the agent via the turbo process or manually if needed.

If you only need one app, use filters (e.g. `pnpm --filter @apparel-commerce/terminal-agent dev`) instead of the root command.
